  abstract={This paper presents the design and implementation of a frequency-modulated continuous wave (FMCW) jamming signal for GPS jamming applications using software-defined radio (SDR). A multiband jammer waveform is designed to target the GPS L1 (1575.42 MHz) and L2 (1227.6 MHz) bands simultaneously through a frequency-hopping method with an inter-band delay. The waveforms are designed using GNU Radio, with the frequency-hopping mechanism integrated through a Python module to provide agile jamming capabilities. The proposed jamming waveforms are analyzed using a spectrum analyzer and transmitted through a commercially available SDR device on a mobile GPS application. The results demonstrate the successful jamming of the GPS receiver in the open environment operating on L1 and L2 frequency bands, highlighting the potential of these designs for agile multiband jamming in defence applications.},
