  abstract={The status of multi UAV cooperative cluster operation in the military field is more and more prominent. Its electronic interference to the radar network is always the focus of military electronic warfare. This paper studies the rules and characteristics of deceptive Jamming of multiple UAVs to radar network, and focuses on how to use the least number of UAVs to generate fake track deception to radar network. This paper starts with the geometric space relationship between the UAV and the radar network. Based on the geometric spatial relationship between the false track of UAV and radar network, a concise mathematical model is established, and the analysis and solution flow of the model is given, which provides important enlightenment for improving the electronic countermeasure capability of the grouped UAV.},
