  pages={252-255},
  abstract={Satellite navigation deception, also known as spoof jamming technology, is crucial as an anti-drone technology being developed alongside the revitalization of the drone industry. Unlike existing simulator-type or non-real-time signal generators, this advanced drone jamming technology combines a spoofing deception signal generator with real-time target information and navigation satellite orbit data. In this study, we outlined the design, manufacturing results, and core real time performance metrics, including time and navigation message synchronization. To validate the possibility of directional guidance of an autonomous UAV through spoofing techniques, we developed a novel deception procedure and successfully demonstrated its effectiveness in controlling the flight direction of an autonomous UAV through spoof jamming.},
  keywords={Satellites;Spaceborne radar;Prototypes;Satellite navigation systems;Signal generators;Autonomous aerial vehicles;Real-time systems;Synchronization;Jamming;Drones;anti-drone;counter-measuring UAV;GNSS spoofing},
