  number={},
  pages={354-357},
  abstract={With the development of society, the development of communication technology has entered a new stage, and it is playing an increasingly important role in people's lives and has become an indispensable part. At the same time, the research direction of communication technology is also changing, among which the research of emergency communication has become one of the most important research directions. Aiming at the problem that the existing synchronization algorithms have a high probability of missing detection in the fast time-varying UAV (unmanned aerial vehicle) channel, this paper proposes a channel estimation-based optimization method for UAV communication link performance. According to the energy change in the sliding window, the position of each path is judged, and then the first path is detected by threshold method or adaptive threshold method. Using GPS positioning information to accurately calculate the minimum mean square, maximum signal-to-noise ratio and minimum variance, and according to the optimal selection criterion, the complex anti-jamming signals can be weakened and eliminated. Finally, through the ground test and air-to-ground test, the UAV data link system is tested by corresponding examples, and the corresponding improvements are made according to the test results. The test also shows the practicability and stability of the system.},
